1 set up git
	I can set up git follow https://help.github.com/articles/set-up-git in Cent OS.

2 creat a repository
	https://help.github.com/articles/create-a-repo
	note: before step3, you should execute the command : git config --global http.sslVerify false. If not execute, may raise an "SSL certificate problem, verify that the CA cert is OK." error 

3 fork
	https://help.github.com/articles/fork-a-repo
	note: git remote add upstream originalURL and git fetch upstream, if you want to new the update of the original code you forked from timely.

4 social
	https://help.github.com/articles/be-social

